    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1758905682" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1758905682" />
    <a title="Helga" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23362895-helga"><img alt="Helga" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1636781485p2/23362895.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1758905682?book_show_action=true">Oct 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Helga" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Helga" href="/user/show/23362895-helga">Helga</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23362895-helga?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23362895-helga?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23362895-helga?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23362895-helga?shelf=crime">crime</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1758905682" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12754691452801979445">4.5<br/><br/><i>“The dead win when you quit singing and let them take you on down the road with them.”</i><br/><br/>What are the weirdest things you’ve ever collected? <br/>I was collecting matchboxes when I was little. Lol. And then I tried to collect stamps and failed. Does collecting chewing gum and candy wrappers go under the category of weird? <br/><br/>Well, let’s compare those with what our hero likes to collect in this story. Serial killers’ sketches, a sixteenth century human skull, a 300 year old confession signed by a witch; </span>
  <span id="freeText12754691452801979445" style="display:none">4.5<br /><br /><i>“The dead win when you quit singing and let them take you on down the road with them.”</i><br /><br />What are the weirdest things you’ve ever collected? <br />I was collecting matchboxes when I was little. Lol. And then I tried to collect stamps and failed. Does collecting chewing gum and candy wrappers go under the category of weird? <br /><br />Well, let’s compare those with what our hero likes to collect in this story. Serial killers’ sketches, a sixteenth century human skull, a 300 year old confession signed by a witch; you want me to go on?<br /><br />So when our hero realizes that a ghost is for sale in an auction, he doesn’t hesitate and puts the highest bid and buys it. But what he receives in the heart-shaped box, is more than the suit of the dead man.<br />Who is the seller of the ghost? Who does this suit belong to? And what is this ghost’s agenda? And more importantly how can our hero get rid of it?</span>
  <a data-text-id="12754691452801979445" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

